---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE_ORIGIN, canonicalAbsolute } from "../lib/site";

const pageTitle = "Buy Supplements Online Singapore | FAQ";
const pageDescription =
  "Frequently asked questions about online supplement listings, seller transparency, and buying context in Singapore.";
const faqPageUrl = canonicalAbsolute("/faq");

const faqItems = [
  {
    q: 'What does "buy supplements online singapore" usually mean?',
    a: "The phrase refers to browsing and purchasing health supplements via the internet with Singapore as the delivery or billing context. It covers marketplace listings, brand sites, and overseas sellers that ship here. It does not name a single regulator-approved storefront. Readers typically want clearer seller identity, ingredient visibility, and shipping terms before they complete a purchase.",
  },
  {
    q: "What seller information is commonly visible on online listings?",
    a: "Common fields include a seller or shop name, business registration where provided, contact options such as email or chat, and policy pages for returns or refunds. Some listings show a registered address. Product blocks add titles, images, price, and descriptive text. Each platform decides which fields are mandatory.",
  },
  {
    q: "Why do people look for importer or distributor information?",
    a: "Importer or distributor lines describe which entity placed the product on the local market. Readers use them to connect packaging claims to a named organisation and to see whether the seller is the brand, an authorised partner, or a reseller. When missing, only the marketplace profile and photos remain to inspect.",
  },
  {
    q: "What does listing completeness usually include?",
    a: "Completeness usually means a clear product name, coherent ingredient or label references, imagery that matches the described pack, price and currency, and shipping or fulfilment notes. Buyers expect alignment between headline, bullet points, and fine print. Missing ingredients, conflicting titles, or generic photos reduce transparent reading of the offer.",
  },
  {
    q: "Why do people search for seller transparency signals?",
    a: "People search when they want a calm checklist for interpreting supplement listing transparency signals without marketing noise. They may be unsure what seller information should be visible or how platform layouts hide key facts. Queries about how to read supplement seller information online seek neutral language for comparing sellers before asking clinicians about personal suitability.",
  },
  {
    q: "Is this site reviewing or recommending products?",
    a: "No. This site publishes educational explanations only. It does not review, rate, rank, or recommend supplements or sellers. Nothing here endorses efficacy or safety outcomes. For personal decisions, qualified clinicians and official product information remain the appropriate sources beyond general listing-reading guidance.",
  },
];

const breadcrumbJsonLd = JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  itemListElement: [
    { "@type": "ListItem", position: 1, name: "Home", item: SITE_ORIGIN },
    { "@type": "ListItem", position: 2, name: "FAQ", item: faqPageUrl },
  ],
});

const webPageJsonLd = JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebPage",
  name: pageTitle,
  url: faqPageUrl,
  description: pageDescription,
  inLanguage: "en-SG",
});

const faqPageJsonLd = JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  mainEntity: faqItems.map((item) => ({
    "@type": "Question",
    name: item.q,
    acceptedAnswer: { "@type": "Answer", text: item.a },
  })),
});
---
<BaseLayout
  title={pageTitle}
  description={pageDescription}
  path="/faq"
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: "Home", href: "/" },
    { name: "FAQ", href: "/faq" },
  ]}
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={breadcrumbJsonLd}></script>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={webPageJsonLd}></script>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={faqPageJsonLd}></script>

  <h1>Buy Supplements Online Singapore: Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

  <div class="disclaimer">
    General educational information only. Not medical or legal advice.
  </div>

  <p>
    When people search to buy supplements online Singapore, they are usually comparing channels that list health supplements for delivery or pickup in Singapore: marketplaces, brand stores, and cross-border sellers.
    Online supplements Singapore pages mix marketing copy with variable amounts of seller identity and label detail.
    A supplement seller Singapore profile may show registration, contacts, and policies, but structure differs by platform.
    On a supplement marketplace Singapore listing, what seller information should be visible is not uniform—buyers often look for supplement listing transparency signals and guidance on how to read supplement seller information online before they interpret prices or imagery.
    This FAQ summarises common reading questions in neutral, non-commercial language.
  </p>

  {faqItems.map((item) => (
    <section>
      <h2>{item.q}</h2>
      <p>{item.a}</p>
    </section>
  ))}

  <h2>Key Takeaway</h2>
  <div class="key-takeaway">
    Reading listings for online supplements Singapore means checking which seller fields the platform exposes, whether ingredients and label references match the images, and whether importer or distributor lines appear.
    Supplement listing transparency signals are strongest when title, text, and imagery stay aligned.
    How to read supplement seller information online is a documentation skill: note what is stated, what is missing, and what would need a follow-up question.
    This site explains patterns; it does not review or recommend specific products.
  </div>

  <h2>Related Context</h2>
  <p>
    For wider background on supplements in Singapore—not seller reviews or product picks—see the
    <a href="https://supplementsingapore.neoi.jp/">Supplements Singapore guide</a>.
  </p>

  <p class="page-note">Educational content only. Not medical or treatment advice.</p>
</BaseLayout>
